                <commentary audience="instructor"><title>Note</title>
                <p>Point out that mixture problems are actually easy: after we fill in the first two columns of the table with information from the problem, we multiply across to get the third column and add down columns 1 and 3 to get the equations.</p></commentary> 

<task><p>Write one equation about the amount of solution Amal needs.</p></task>

